summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2006 JEEP LIBERTY. THE CONTACT STATED THAT THEY PARKED THE VEHICLE AND SHUT THE ENGINE OFF, BUT COULD NOT TAKE THE KEY OUT OF THE IGNITION SWITCH. THE CONTACT WAS A MECHANIC AND NOTICED THE SHIFTING CABLE WAS LOOSE AND PUSHED IT BACK IN WHICH ALLOWED HIM TO TAKE THE KEY OUT OF THE IGNITION. THE DEALER WAS NOTIFIED OF THE FAILURE. THE VEHICLE WAS NOT REPAIRED. THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOT MADE AWARE OF THE FAILURE. THE APPROXIMATE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 80,000.    UPDATED 5/4/15*CN
